    	<div class="comment_content">
    		<p>What people don&#8217;t get about Steve Jobs is that he wasn&#8217;t trying to run a spa for his employees. He was trying to take care of his end users. That&#8217;s who mattered to Jobs, and that&#8217;s why Apple has been so incredibly successful over his second tenure. Look at any customer satisfaction metric you want in the industries Apple participates in. And look which company leads the list. It&#8217;s not that complicated. Apple under Jobs delivered what most other companies give lip service to: a passionate, almost fanatical dedication to customer satisfaction.</p>

