    	<div class="comment_content">
    		<p>If it doesn&#8217;t work and It results in No successes, your leadership style, whatever it may be, . . . is wrong.</p>
<p>If it succeeds, . . . it&#8217;s right.</p>
<p>Steve&#8217;s was right.</p>
<p>Hundreds, if not thousands, of talented employees were sliced and diced, and still feel the pain of Steve&#8217;s sword, yet in the end, his maniacal dedication to what HE was convinced was right, repeatedly delivered successes which swept away memories of the failures.</p>
<p>The result is NOT a methodology of leadership that should be admired, but a whole organization that designs, produces, and markets, products and image, better than any single company on the planet.</p>

