    	<div class="comment_content">
    		<p>It&#8217;s amazing how unconscious our culture and the people that comprise it are. Look at the way journalist are praising and worshiping Steve Jobs, who was successful at creating electronic devices but an abject failure in his dealings with people. You don&#8217;t measure success with interpersonal relationships by how much $$$ one has earned. Jobs, like many business CEOs is a classic narcissist&#8230;and a toxic, malignant one at that. Berating and demeaning people is not in any way normal or the least bit acceptable. That type of behavior is repugnant and hurts people at a deep psycho-spiritual level. It&#8217;s amazing but does not surprise me to see people putting Jobs up on a pedestal, since 99% of Americans are afflicted with narcissism, which is the human condition. Our psycho-spiritual diseases manifest as physical illness and follow the dictum &#8220;as above, so below.&#8221; With Jobs toxic sub human treatment of people, it is not surprising at all to see him literally eaten up by cancer.</p>

